I run a small café and on busy days it's a mess — people walk in while the phone is ringing for a booking, my staff can't tell who's next, and customers leave because they don't know how long they'll wait. I'd love a simple app or something that helps us handle bookings and the walk-in queue without it being two separate things in my head. I'd also like customers to be able to book a table through the app themselves so the phone isn't ringing during the rush. Mostly for me and the people on the floor; would be nice if regulars feel taken care of too.
